commit.message: Start to add some smoke tests.
Revert changes to shadow implementation from  bf04f5144fea36a0200ab811ee02b4646dfb4d37
Add 'sp_loginclass' to retrieve the user's login class

Merge pull request #20 from bsiegert/master

MirBSD and NetBSD support

Remove requirement for getpwnam_r.

The function is never called. MirBSD does not have it.

Support MirBSD and NetBSD, like FreeBSD and OpenBSD.

Also simplify the table in the readme file; the supported set of
features is the same for all BSDs.
Change name to match name used in pwd/shadow.c

Fix up issue with shadow implementation.

When the implementations were split into shadow and pwd, the code
initialzing the structure used in the shadow implementation was replaced
by older code not including the added field, always nil in that
implemenation, for pw_change.

The intent currently is that the passwdEntry structure should contain
all the fields available across implementations.
Extract structure creation code into a method.

Merge pull request #17 from jasperla/openbsd

Add OpenBSD support

Attempt to resolve BSD make issues.

The depend file was using ifneq statements in it, which was not
compatible with BSD's make.  Looking around at some other gems, it
doesn't seem to be standard to include ruby headers in the actual make
file.  This removes the check for ruby.h and ruby(/?)io.h in the
makefile, and adds a check into extconf.rb.

Remove the sgetspent method from the pwd impl.

FreeBSD and OS X do not implement an equivalent to sgetspent, and the
implementation included before did not work as expected.

sgetspent is supposed to parse a shadow user data in a string and return the first
entry. The implementation we had called getpwnam (in the pwd version), with the
supplied string which meant it was trying to find a user with a name equal to the
passed in shadow file string.

it's best to just remove the function all together.
Add LICENSE to MANIFEST, something that should have been done with 8d4b36008a34529ef1e1d56a7f37d0e398e23894
